{"word":"G3107 - μακάριος - makários - mak-ar'-ee-os - Blessed","slug":"G3107","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">μακάριος</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>makários"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>mak-ar'-ee-os"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Blessed"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03BC;&#x03B1;&#x03BA;&#x03B1;&#x0301;&#x03C1;&#x03B9;&#x03BF;&#x03C2; - makarios</b> - <i>mak-ar'-ee-os</i><p/>A prolonged form of the poetical <b>&#x03BC;&#x03B1;&#x0301;&#x03BA;&#x03B1;&#x03C1;</b> <b>makar</b> (meaning the same); supremely <i>blest</i>; by extension <i>fortunate</i>, <i>well off:</i> - blessed, happy (X -ier)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G3106\">G3106</a>, <a href=\"#/G3108\">G3108</a>"}]}